http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/Burglars-break-into-house/article13987693.ece

Burglars struck at a locked house and decamped with gold and silver ornaments worth Rs. 2 lakh at BSR Nagar in Aswaraopet around midnight on Wednesday.The incident came to light when the owner of the house, Murthy Raju, an LIC agent, returned home along with his family after attending a function at his close relative's house in the small hours of Thursday, sources said. They found the front door lock broken and valuables, including 80 grams of gold and silver articles weighing about a kilogramme, besides several silk sarees, missing. The Aswaraopet police pressed into service the Clues Team and initiated a detailed investigation into the incident.